I have seen two specimens of [
Scorpio cavimanus
]—one (dried) brought from Kilima-Njaro by Mr. M. J. Jackson; the other, which, being preserved in spirit of wine, I have selected as the type , brought by Capt. Speke from Umyamuezi.... The specimen from Kilima-Njaro is smaller and slightly less granular than the other.
